---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/layout/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/layout/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions"
  description="Terms and Conditions for True Finance Tools. Read our terms of use, disclaimers, and conditions for using our free FIRE calculator and financial tools."
  canonical="https://truefinancetools.com/terms"
  keywords="terms and conditions, terms of use, true finance tools terms, calculator disclaimer"
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-hairline bg-canvas py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <p class="mb-4 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          Terms &amp; Conditions
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-body">Last updated: June 9, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <article class="bg-canvas py-12 sm:py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none space-y-8 text-body">

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
            <p>By accessing and using True Finance Tools (the "Website"), you accept and agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our Website.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">2. Description of Service</h2>
            <p>True Finance Tools provides free financial calculators and educational content related to Financial Independence and Early Retirement (FIRE). Our tools include, but are not limited to:</p>
            <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-sm text-body">
              <li>FIRE Calculator (Lean, Regular, Fat, Coast, and Barista FIRE)</li>
              <li>Educational articles about FIRE strategies and financial independence</li>
              <li>Interactive charts and projections</li>
              <li>PDF export and sharing features</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">3. Important Disclaimer</h2>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-warning bg-warning-soft p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink">This calculator provides estimates only.</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-body">The results generated by our calculators are for informational and educational purposes only. They should not be considered financial advice, investment recommendations, or guarantees of future performance. Always consult with a qualified financial advisor before making financial decisions.</p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">4. No Financial Advice</h2>
            <p>The information and tools provided on this Website are not intended to be a substitute for professional financial advice. We are not financial advisors, and nothing on this Website should be construed as financial, investment, tax, or legal advice.</p>
            <p>Past performance of any investment does not guarantee future results. All investments involve risk, including possible loss of principal.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">5. Assumptions and Limitations</h2>
            <p>Our FIRE calculator makes certain assumptions, including but not limited to:</p>
            <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-sm text-body">
              <li>Constant rate of return (actual returns will vary)</li>
              <li>Stable inflation rate over the projection period</li>
              <li>No major life changes affecting income or expenses</li>
              <li>No unexpected expenses or financial windfalls</li>
              <li>Current tax laws remain unchanged</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Real-world results will differ from projections. Market volatility, economic changes, and personal circumstances can significantly impact actual outcomes.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">6. User Responsibilities</h2>
            <p>By using this Website, you agree to:</p>
            <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-sm text-body">
              <li>Use the Website only for lawful purposes</li>
              <li>Not attempt to interfere with the Website's functionality</li>
              <li>Not use automated systems to access the Website without permission</li>
              <li>Verify all calculations independently before making financial decisions</li>
              <li>Consult qualified professionals for personalized financial advice</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p>All content on this Website, including text, graphics, logos, icons, images, data compilations, and software, is the property of True Finance Tools or its content suppliers and is protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.</p>
            <p>You may not reproduce, distribute, modify, or create derivative works from any content without prior written permission.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, True Finance Tools shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or revenues, arising from:</p>
            <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-sm text-body">
              <li>Your use of or reliance on the calculator results</li>
              <li>Financial decisions made based on information from this Website</li>
              <li>Inaccuracies or errors in the calculator or content</li>
              <li>Unauthorized access to or alteration of your data</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">9. Privacy</h2>
            <p>Your use of this Website is also governed by our <a href="/privacy" class="text-link hover:text-link-deep underline">Privacy Policy</a>. By using the Website, you consent to the collection and use of information as described in the Privacy Policy.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">10. Modifications to Terms</h2>
            <p>We reserve the right to modify these Terms and Conditions at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting on this page. Your continued use of the Website after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the new terms.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">11. Governing Law</h2>
            <p>These Terms and Conditions shall be governed by and construed in accordance with applicable laws, without regard to conflict of law principles.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">12. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about these Terms and Conditions, please contact us:</p>
            <ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-sm text-body">
              <li>By visiting our <a href="/contact" class="text-link hover:text-link-deep underline">Contact page</a></li>
              <li>By email: contact@truefinancetools.com</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
